    "display_name": "Paint a Donut",
    "project_template_level_name": "CSA U1L6-PainterPlus PBT_alt-2025",
    "long_instructions": "Move, turn right, and paint. Then, move and paint again. Do this until the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">PainterPlus</code> has painted a donut shape.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** Write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">moveTurnPaint()</code> and use it in The Neighborhood.\r\n\r\n1. In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">PainterPlus.java</code>, write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">moveTurnPaint</code> with the parameter <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String color</code> to have a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Painter</code> object:\r\n\r\n   a. Move\r\n   \r\n   b. Turn right\r\n   \r\n   c. Paint\r\n   \r\n   d. Move\r\n   \r\n   e. Paint\r\n\r\n2. In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">NeighborhoodRunner.java</code>, use your <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">moveTurnPaint()</code> method to navigate in The Neighborhood.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with writing a method or a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">while</code> loop.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n📝 **COMMENT:** Be sure to add comments to note what your code does.\r\n\r\n🖥️ **TEST:** Test your program to check if your code achieves the expected result.\r\n\r\n🎉 **RUN:** Run your program to see the result of your code!\r\n\r\n**Note**: Code that you have written previously for the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">PainterPlus</code> class will be seen here.\r\n\r\n## 🎯 Goal\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/25290a143ab737f29458dc94c72e0755-image-1666028241766.gif)",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Write the method `moveTurnPaint()` to move, turn, and paint.",
